---SECURITY INCIDENT REPORT---

Incident ID: 19
Reported By: Braulio Garcia - Tier 1 SOC Analyst 
Date: February 28, 2026
Time Detected: 03:40 PST
Severity: Critical
Status: Escalated to Tier 2
Attack Technique: Exploitation for Privilege Escalation


1. Executive Summary

  On February 28th at 03:40 PM, an alert was generated by the SIEM, involving a detection of privilege escalation from an internal user Katherine (KatharinePRD) endpoint device (IP: 172.16.15.78).
  After endpoint analysis of the user's processes history, a suspicious filename 'creditcard' was found in the process path, it was also found that the process spawned from the home directory.
  A VirusTotal lookup of the attached file hash '7299c49dd85069e47d6514ab5e10c264' confirmed association with known exploit CVE-2017-16995, a Linux kernel privilege escalation vulnerability.
  Due to the nature of this known exploit, all malware and privilege escalation events were executed locally in the user's device. Notable absence of browser history and network activity
  on the incident date suggests possible log tampering or evidence deletion, though this remains unconfirmed pending Tier 2 forensic analysis. This incident was recognized as only the
  beginning of an attack kill chain, the affected endpoint was isolated and the incident was immediately escalated to Tier 2 for further imapact assessment.


2. Timeline of Events 

  Time (PST)           Event
  03:40              SIEM alert triggered 
